albumData.title: 150828 Changing Dagmars bedding and discovering she molted

media.description:
I removed Dagmar in her log enclosure with all her web bedding. 
I moved all of it to a large plastic container while I cleaned the old material out of her tank.
If you look carefully, you can see her molted skin behind her in the log.
This was her second molt since we got her.
media.title: 20150828_182701.jpg

media.description:
Sorry its blurry, I was in a hurry.
Fresh clean peat moss and water in a cleaned out tank!
media.title: 20150828_183858.jpg

media.description: She tends to hide and sulk after cleaning out her tank.

media.description:
Sometimes it takes a wile for her to get used to fresh bedding and she will prefer to hang on the side of her tank.
We went through this when we tried to use shredded coconut husk material - she HATED that stuff.
I can clearly see now she grew and is a little bigger.

media.description: This brings new meaning to Nu-Skin!

media.description:
It's hard to see here but she caught a cricket.
That's a really good sign that she is comfortable in her freshened home.
